# Note: source PDFs in Patents/ ARE tracked (small, provenance-critical).
# Large datasets are intentionally excluded; record pointers/provenance in evidence/sources/.

# --- Reproducible sanity-check artifacts (regenerate via forward-model/viz/) ---
# Metrics + "what to look for" live in the committed sanity report; the heavy
# self-contained viz HTML (inlined Plotly) and the NetCDF results are regenerable.
**/validation/sanity/viz/*.html
**/validation/sanity/data/
# Sequential overland sign-off: heavy self-contained HTML + the run npz are regenerable
# (forward-model/viz/run_sequential_overland_signoff.py + make_sequential_overland_signoff_html.py).
technologies/infiltration-runoff-model/forward-model/viz/sequential_overland_signoff__*.html
technologies/infiltration-runoff-model/forward-model/scratch/sequential_overland_signoff.npz
# Overland partition-bug investigation (2026-06-24): regenerable run outputs + the monolith-target
# cache. The diagnostic .py reproductions ARE tracked; their console/npz outputs are not.
technologies/infiltration-runoff-model/forward-model/scratch/seq_iter_*.txt
technologies/infiltration-runoff-model/forward-model/scratch/seq_iter_*.npz
technologies/infiltration-runoff-model/forward-model/scratch/seq_iter_*.log
technologies/infiltration-runoff-model/forward-model/scratch/hardening_xfail_check.txt

# --- Benchmark comparison artifacts (regenerate via benchmarks/build_comparison_*.py) ---
# Same rationale: the heavy self-contained comparison HTML (inlined Plotly, ~6 MB each) and the
# NetCDF summaries are regenerable from the committed decks + builders. Track the code, not blobs.
technologies/infiltration-runoff-model/benchmarks/html/
technologies/infiltration-runoff-model/benchmarks/data/
